# üì° Ridera Protocol ‚Äì API Documentation

This document describes the Ridera backend API used by the SRU Engine, Staking Dashboard, and Beta Testing Panel.

---

# üîê Authentication

Most endpoints require an *API token* or *signed wallet message*.

Header:

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Wallet-auth header:

X-Wallet: <address> X-Signature: <signedMessage>

---

# üìò Endpoints Overview

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ *SRU Engine Endpoints*

### *POST /sru/submit*
Submit SRU data for a cycle.

*Body:*
```json
{
  "cycleId": 47,
  "userWallet": "0xABC...",
  "platform": "Swiggy",
  "region": "india",
  "earnings": 1200,
  "generatedSru": 22
}

Response:

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "SRU submitted"
}


---

GET /sru/user/{wallet}

Get all SRU entries for a user.

Response:

{
  "wallet": "0xABC...",
  "totalSRU": 99,
  "cycles": [
    {
      "cycleId": 47,
      "sru": 22,
      "earnings": 1200
    }
  ]
}


---

2Ô∏è‚É£ Proof Registry Endpoints

GET /registry/cycle/{id}

Fetch cycle data stored in contract.

Response:

{
  "cycleId": 47,
  "merkleRoot": "0x73655...",
  "totalSRU": 9000,
  "timestamp": 173456222
}


---

POST /registry/submit

Submit merkle root for a cycle.

Body:

{
  "cycleId": 47,
  "merkleRoot": "0xAAA123...",
  "totalSRU": 8200
}


---

3Ô∏è‚É£ Staking Endpoints

GET /staking/user/{wallet}

Fetch user staking info.

Response:

{
  "wallet": "0xABC...",
  "staked": 1000,
  "pendingRewards": 44,
  "claimedCycles": [45, 46]
}


---

POST /staking/stake

Stake RDRT tokens.

Body:

{
  "wallet": "0xABC...",
  "amount": 500
}


---

POST /staking/claim

Claim rewards for all cycles.


---

4Ô∏è‚É£ Yield Vault Endpoints

POST /vault/process

Process rewards for a cycle.

Body:

{
  "cycleId": 47
}

Response:

{
  "message": "Processed successfully",
  "cycleId": 47,
  "rewardDistributed": 5000
}


---

üìä Error Response Format

{
  "success": false,
  "error": "Invalid cycle ID"
}


---

üß™ Rate Limits

60 requests/min per IP

120 requests/min per authenticated wallet



---

‚ö† Disclaimer

This API is for beta phase only.
Endpoints may change during audits and pre-mainnet launch.
